<Class name="CM_JRWCamTransaction" id="f02a6117-59d3-4974-b9ce-50f9df4773b8">
    <superclass name="CM_JRWTransaction"/>
    <transient/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>
27/7/09 JMH  MES 1011 JMT to CICS Interfaces
This new subclass will be used for the transients passed to the JRW report to create extract file.
 The reference to myCamFile also allows reference to Cam Protocol properties.</text>
    <DbClassMap file="query"/>
    <ImplicitInverseRef name="allEventTransactions" id="9c86bdaa-58d8-447f-b0fd-874ebf19fa94">
        <memberTypeInverse/>
        <type name="CM_EventTransByDateTime"/>
    </ImplicitInverseRef>
    <ExplicitInverseRef name="myCamFile" id="9ef22e50-4d11-4abf-87ae-2b5676f0f8b2">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="CM_CamFile"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>
The report needs a ref to the CamProtocol, so we will pass the CamFile cause this will provide a ref to CamProtocol as well as allow us to pass additional information to the CM_JRWTransaction </text>
        <Inverse name="CM_CamFileJRW::myJRWCamTransaction"/>
    </ExplicitInverseRef>
</Class>
